      "title": "Widen IN subqueries to one-column grouped or aggregate outputs",
      "agent": "implementer",
      "modelProfile": "balanced",
      "prompt": "Lift the current SQL-like IN-subquery restriction in a bounded way. Allow a subquery with exactly one explicit select field to participate in WHERE IN even when the subquery uses GROUP BY and/or HAVING, as long as it stays uncorrelated and join-free. Keep the change narrow: no correlated subqueries, no EXISTS, no scalar-subquery generalization, and no join support. Update value extraction so the outer filter reads the selected output name rather than only the raw source field name. Preserve the current rejection of multiple select fields and unsupported window/computed subquery shapes. Add or adjust tests to prove one grouped or aggregate one-column subquery works end to end and that rejected shapes still fail with a clear message.",
